0even%20sure%20I%20found%20it%20socially%20challenging.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENagle%20was%20homeschooled%20by%20both%20of%20her%20parents%20in%20California%20from%20the%20age%20of%2010%20through%20college.%20Now%20self-employed%20in%20jewelry%20design%2C%20the%20Gen%20Xer%20said%20she's%20grateful%20for%20her%20homeschool%20experience%20because%20her%20parents%20tailored%20her%20lessons%20to%20meet%20her%20learning%20pace%20and%20interests%2C%20and%20she%20said%20the%20personalized%20curriculum%20led%20her%20to%20excel%20in%20national%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20her%20parents%20didn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-high-schools-changing-value-of-college-trade-higher-education-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epush%20for%20an%20elite%20college%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20step%20to%20success%20later%20in%20life%2C%20which%20empowered%20Nagle%20to%20attend%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%20on%20a%20scholarship%20in%20the%20late%2090s%20before%20transferring%20to%20San%20Francisco%20State%20University%20instead%20of%20taking%20out%20student%20loans%20to%20pursue%20a%20more%20prestigious%20school.%20She%20said%20the%20lack%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-repayment-overhaul-gen-z-credit-scores-inflation-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estudent%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20defining%20characteristic%20that%20separates%20her%20from%20many%20of%20her%20peers%2C%20and%20she's%20grateful%20that%20she%20didn't%20have%20the%20pressure%20that%20students%20at%20public%20schools%20often%20face%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprincipal-at-high-school-doesnt-push-college-why-it-works-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eattend%20more%20expensive%20colleges%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20parents%20always%20told%20me%20that%20you%20shouldn't%20make%20college%20the%20be-all%20and%20end-all%20of%20your%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Nagle%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20realize%20my%20life%20is%20really%20different%20from%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20friends%20who%20went%20to%20their%20dream%20school%20and%20have%20just%20still%20tons%20of%20student%20loan%20debt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENagle's%20jewelry%20business%20has%20generated%20nearly%20%2429%2C000%20in%20sales%20in%20September%20and%20just%20over%20%24115%2C500%20year-to-date%2C%20according%20to%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20She%20made%20%24121%2C000%20in%20sales%20the%20year%20prior.%20She%20said%20that%20hers%20can%20be%20an%20%26quot%3Berratic%20business%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20her%20sales%20fluctuate%2C%20with%20August%2C%20September%2C%20and%20March%20typically%20being%20her%20busiest%20months.%20She%20says%20she%20prioritizes%20reinvesting%20in%20her%20business%20%E2%80%94%20like%20buying%20new%20equipment%20%E2%80%94%20over%20paying%20herself.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20she%20said%2C%20her%20annual%20income%20is%20in%20the%20high%20five%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomeschooling%20in%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-homeschooling-on-the-rise-vouchers-public-school-education-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eis%20on%20the%20rise%3C%2Fa%3E.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20number%20of%20parents%20choosing%20to%20teach%20their%20kids%20at%20home%20surged%20due%20to%20dissatisfaction%20with%20remote%20learning%2C%20and%20that%20trend%20never%20went%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growth%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-vouchers-school-choice-block-grants-public-funding-private-education-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eschool%20voucher%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20increased%20availability%20of%20federal%20funds%20to%20use%20for%20education%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-microschool-pros-cons-personalized-learning-new-education-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eother%20than%20public%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20homeschools%20or%20microschools%2C%20are%20contributing%20to%20the%20increased%20interest%20in%20alternative%20forms%20of%20schooling.%20Still%2C%20public%20school%20enrollment%20remains%20dominant%3B%2049.5%20million%20students%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnces.ed.gov%2Fwhatsnew%2Fpress_releases%2F12_5_2024.asp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenrolled%20in%20public%20schools%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20fall%20of%202023%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnces.ed.gov%2Fuse-work%2Fresource-library%2Freport%2Ffirst-look-ed-tab%2Fparent-and-family-involvement-education-2023%3Fpubid%3D2024113%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapproximately%203%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20were%20homeschooled%20that%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20being%20homeschooled%2C%20Nagle%20said%20she%20attended%20a%20public%20school%20briefly%2C%20but%20her%20parents%20were%20dissatisfied%20with%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20local%20schools.%20She%20said%20it%20was%20difficult%20to%20hear%20criticism%20of%20homeschooling%20and%20the%20notion%20that%20kids%20like%20herself%20wouldn't%20have%20the%20skills%20to%20succeed%20socially%20or%20academically%2C%20but%20looking%20back%2C%20she's%20glad%20she's%20able%20to%20prove%20those%20critics%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20made%20me%20really%20think%20things%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20Nagle%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20realize%20that%20sometimes%2C%20even%20though%20everybody's%20saying%20one%20thing%2C%20they%20can%20all%20be%20wrong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20your%20educational%20experience%2C%20or%20educational%20choices%20you're%20making%20for%20your%20kids%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3A%2520asheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f295466-aec1-4ee0-9370-ad3da5d03015%5C%22%3E'It's%20not%20a%20fringe%20decision%20anymore'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EData%20compiled%20by%20Johns%20Hopkins'%20Homeschool%20Research%20Lab%20found%20that%2017%20states%20have%20so%20far%20reported%20increases%20in%20homeschooling%20in%20the%202024-25%20school%20year.%20It%20follows%2019%20states%20that%20reported%20homeschooling%20increases%20in%20the%20year%20prior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAngela%20Watson%2C%20creator%20of%20the%20research%20lab%20and%20senior%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Johns%20Hopkins%20Institute%20for%20Education%20Policy%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bnow%20we%20see%20that%20people%20who%20choose%20to%20homeschool%20their%20children%20are%20slightly%20younger%20than%20their%20private%20school%20or%20public%20schooling%20parent%20peers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20it%20could%20be%20that%20this%20is%20kind%20of%20a%20younger%20generation%20thing%20where%20it's%20not%20stigmatized%20for%20them%20in%20the%20same%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Watson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%20do%20not%20report%20homeschooling%20data%2C%20and%20since%20each%20state%20has%20different%20homeschooling%20laws%20%E2%80%94%20including%20whether%20parents%20can%20receive%20federal%20dollars%20to%20homeschool%20%E2%80%94%20it%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20regulate.%20Even%20so%2C%20Nagle%20said%2C%20the%20rise%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20homeschooling%20among%20the%20states%20that%20do%20report%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-high-school-students-are-graduating-with-work-experience-college-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eit's%20a%20type%20of%20education%3C%2Fa%3E%20that's%20become%20more%20accepted%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20less%20stigmatized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20minority%20decision%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20a%20fringe%20decision%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20Nagle%20said.%20She%2