20different%20flavor%20and%20type%20of%20client%20relationships%20to%20the%20business.%20We%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20support%2C%20but%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20resistance.%20The%20first%2015%20minutes%20of%20every%20conversation%20were%20crucial%2C%20because%20I%20had%20to%20really%20prove%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20my%20mid-twenties%2C%20blonde%2C%20and%20not%20even%205'2%2C%20so%20some%20of%20the%20guys%20on%20the%20trading%20desk%20questioned%20why%20I%20was%20excelling.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20I%20got%20laser%20eye%20surgery%2C%20but%20I%20kept%20wearing%20glasses%20for%20a%20while%20to%20look%20a%20bit%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220190c6fc-14e9-46a8-8e87-b5630008fe9e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETravel%20was%20exciting%2C%20but%20it%20took%20a%20toll%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Brazil%2C%20our%20team%20worked%20on%20investor%20services%2C%20so%20I%20interacted%20with%20many%20companies%20and%20funds%20%E2%80%94%20the%20guys%20would%20usually%20choose%20to%20go%20to%20barbecue%20dinners%2C%20the%20club%2C%20and%20golf%20games%20with%20clients%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20relate%20to%20these%20topics%20to%20remain%20included.%20In%20the%20early%20years%2C%20travel%20was%20thrilling%2C%20as%20I%20went%20from%20trips%20within%20Brazil%20to%20global%20journeys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20I%20generally%20had%20a%20nine-to-seven%20schedule%20(except%20for%20the%20nights%20when%20I%20worked%20until%201%20am)%2C%20but%20the%20travel%20started%20to%20take%20a%20toll.%20My%20six-year%20relationship%20ended%20because%20I%20rarely%20saw%20my%20boyfriend%3B%20I%20missed%20birthdays%20and%20Mother's%20Day%3B%20I%20never%20wanted%20to%20take%20trips%20during%20my%20time%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pay%20was%20great%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20have%20time%20for%20hobbies%20or%20the%20gym%2C%20so%20I'd%20overdo%20it%20with%20sports%20on%20the%20weekends.%20Then%20I'd%20spend%20money%20at%20the%20spa%20trying%20to%20relax%2C%20or%20on%20acupuncture%20to%20compensate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wilma%20Ramony%20de%20Souza%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68dff9375dbc4fd10daa24bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Ede%20Souza%20in%20the%20glasses%20she%20would%20sometimes%20wear%20to%20look%20older%20in%20the%20Sao%20Paulo%20office.%3Cp%3EWilma%20Ramony%20de%20Souza%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb9b708b-7824-43a9-8e7a-c85b6415128d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuccess%20in%20New%20York%20was%20addictive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20accomplishments%20were%20like%20a%20drug%3A%20the%20more%20I%20conquered%2C%20the%20more%20I%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20boss%20and%20I%20were%20securing%20big%20clients%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20mind%20approving%20things%20at%201%20am%20as%20long%20as%20we%20got%20the%20accounts%20open.%20All%20I%20saw%20was%20more%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20more%20successful%20we%20became%2C%20the%20more%20attention%20we%20received%2C%20and%20some%20questioned%20whether%20we%20were%20asking%20for%20or%20doing%20too%20much.%20The%20recognition%20was%20amazing%2C%20but%20it%20also%20left%20no%20room%20for%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20City%20in%202019%20as%20a%20Vice%20President%2C%20I%20went%20from%20my%20comfort%20zone%20to%20the%20eye%20of%20the%20storm%2C%20and%20had%20to%20prove%20myself%20even%20more%20as%20a%20foreigner.%20Soon%2C%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20and%20I%20moved%20to%20Miami.%20By%20the%20time%20we%20returned%20to%20the%20office%2C%20I%20was%20flying%20from%20Florida%20to%20New%20York%2C%20until%20eventually%20the%20company%20said%20I%20had%20to%20come%20back%20to%20New%20York%20full-time%20or%20look%20for%20something%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20I%20began%20searching%20for%20jobs%20on%20the%20private%20banking%20side%20of%20the%20business%20and%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20London%20with%20my%20significant%20other.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20betraying%20my%20boss%20when%20I%20told%20her%20I%20was%20leaving%20the%20team%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20want%20her%20job%20one%20day%20or%20the%20life%20of%20a%20Managing%20Director.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22457c8900-3508-4ad2-841b-fa669d3db3b3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBurnout%20caught%20up%20to%20me%20in%20London%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20signs%20of%20burnout%20before%20even%20arriving%20in%20London%3A%20I%20had%20a%20mild%20panic%20attack%20in%20the%20office%20in%20December%202022%20while%20managing%20a%20major%20deal.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20my%20relationship%20was%20struggling%2C%20and%20my%20mom%20thought%20I'd%20never%20be%20back%20for%20another%20Christmas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%20panic%20attack%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20starting%20to%20lose%20both%20my%20health%20and%20myself.%20The%20bank%20would%20always%20give%20me%20more%2C%20but%20it%20was%20my%20job%20to%20know%20how%20much%20was%20enough.%20It%20was%20hard%2C%20though%2C%20being%20in%20a%20place%20where%20asking%20for%20help%20could%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20moved%20to%20London%20in%202023%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20huge%20culture%20shock.%20People%20and%20the%20weather%20were%20colder%2C%20and%20the%20society%20was%20more%20closed%20off.%20I%20found%20it%20harder%20to%20make%20friends%2C%20and%20work%20started%20to%20feel%20meaningless.%20My%20spark%20diminished%2C%20I'd%20feel%20nauseous%20at%20my%20desk%2C%20and%20depression%20crept%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20a%20year%20in%20therapy%20realizing%20I%20was%20no%20longer%20happy%20in%20banking%2C%20and%20another%20two%20months%20gathering%20the%20courage%20to%20resign.%20There%20wasn't%20a%20planned%20date%2C%20but%20I%20just%20walked%20in%20one%20day%20and%20told%20my%20boss%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20leave.%20I%20don't%20just%20blame%20the%20management%20or%20the%20structure%20in%20London.%20I%20take%20full%20responsibility%20for%20my%20part%2C%20having%20accumulated%20so%20much%20baggage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226ee684b9-710f-4ad6-90b5-6ce3b5ec6be7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERediscovering%20myself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20leaving%20for%20good%20in%20November%202024%2C%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20myself.%20There%20was%20no%20other%20job%2C%20no%20alternate%20dream.%20I%20spent%20six%20months%20traveling%2C%20figuring%20out%20who%20I%20was%20and%20what%20I%20loved.%20I%20was%20so%20used%20to%20introducing%20myself%20as%2C%20'Wilma%2C%20who%20works%20at%20JPMorgan.'%20I%20didn't%20know%20who%20Wilma%20was%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20change%20a%20single%20thing%20about%20my%2014%20years%20at%20the%20bank%2C%20though.%20Obviously%2C%20I%20had%20my%20struggles%2C%20my%20stress%2C%20my%20lost%20relationships%2C%20but%20the%20company%20taught%20me%20what%20it%20means%20to%20challenge%20myself%20every%20day%20and%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20be%20excellent.%20Now%2C%20I'm%20living%20mainly%20in%20Miami%2C%20serving%20as%20a%20CEO%20and%20starting%20a%20consulting%20company%20for%20founders%20and%20small%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20I%20even%20gladly%20refer%20some%20of%20them%20to%20JPMorgan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-banker-shares-burnout-lessons-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1759654381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68dec42dcc993f9955cf68ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-banker-shares-burnout-lessons-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Wilma%20Ramony%20de%20Souza%20became%20an%20executive%20director%20by%20her%20thirties%20and%20worked%20across%20the%20world%2C%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20excel%20in%20male-dominated%20offices.%22%2C%22autho